Executive Summary
GRA is embarking on a transformational PoC to digitize informal sector taxation using WhatsApp, USSD, AI-assisted bookkeeping, geospatial intelligence, OSINT, and multilingual accessibility.

Chat Nation proposes a world-class, government-grade system built around four pillars:

1. Identification
Multi-signal identity inference (Ghana Card, phone, OSINT, geospatial clustering, business category inference)
Low-literacy onboarding (voice, Twi/Ga/Ewe)

2. Bookkeeping
WhatsApp text + voice bookkeeping
USSD numeric bookkeeping
AI extraction from speech, images, and receipts

3. Tax Computation
Automatic MTS tax calculation
Filing workflows across all channels
Supervisor controls and audit trails

4. Insights & Governance
Officer dashboards
Market heatmaps
Compliance analytics
Real-time risk scoring

All 12 technical domains have been designed in alignment with:

Ghana Data Protection Act
GRA CDTAS policies
GovStack, e-Gov global standards
World Bank digital public infrastructure frameworks





Technical Document 1 : GRA API Integration Architecture
1. Introduction
This document defines how we will integrate the Proof of Concept (PoC) with the Ghana Revenue Authority (GRA) Core Domestic Tax Administration System (CDTAS) using secure, modular, and standards-aligned APIs.
The integration supports:
Registration


Identity validation


MTS tax computation


Filing submission


Business identification insights


Officer dashboards


This architecture ensures:
No disruption to GRA production systems


Full compliance with data governance laws


Secure one-way or mocked data flows for PoC


2. Integration Goals
Enable informal-sector users to self-register via WhatsApp/USSD.


Use Ghana Card (NIA) data for taxpayer identity verification.


Fetch existing taxpayer records where permitted.


Submit pre-filled tax returns to a sandbox CDTAS endpoint.


Provide GRA officers with real-time PoC dashboard access.


Maintain secure, auditable API calls with full traceability.


3. Integration Principles
Principle
Description
Security-first
Encryption (TLS 1.3), OAuth2.0 client credentials, strict RBAC
Non-intrusive
PoC integrates into sandbox; production systems remain untouched
Modular
Each function (registration, filing, identification) is a separate API component
Interoperable
Aligns with GovStack Information Mediator building block
Low-tech compatible
Designed to support WhatsApp, USSD, SMS, and WhatsApp Voice


