Technical Document #8 — Multi-Channel Strategy
1. Introduction
Ghana’s informal sector spans a wide digital spectrum, requiring a solution that adapts to diverse user behaviors and technology environments:

Many taxpayers prefer WhatsApp due to its familiar, data-lite interface and the fact that it requires no additional app installation.

Others rely heavily on USSD, particularly users with low literacy, limited data access, or basic feature phones.

There is a a portion responds best to SMS reminders, which reach users in all regions and on all device types.

Low-literacy and rural users often prefer voice-based interaction, best delivered through WhatsApp Business API Voice, which replaces traditional IVR with a more intuitive, accessible experience.

A national-scale tax digitization system must therefore operate seamlessly across all major communication channels, ensuring that taxpayers are not forced into a single digital pathway.

